      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Now officially within their relationship, Falke finds something inescapable about herself holding her back from what her heart yearns for.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;(This is a sequel to The Dreamers Wake.)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1332653-but-my-mind-holds-the-key/chapter/1332655/"&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;God Lives&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Falke sat on the couch with a novel, trying to keep her eyes on the unfolding storyline before her and not have them wandering off to the bedroom door just around the corner. She couldn’t hear them, not all the time, but she could feel them constantly, could almost picture the sweet-talking, kissing, biting, and thrusting in her head. She lowered her eyes to the book and turned a page, but a sudden jolt rippled through her torso and arms, making her shake the book, and what followed after was the quiet, but unmistakable growl of a low-pitched moan. Whether it had come from Elster or Ariane, she couldn’t tell, but Falke had felt it before she had heard it. She sighed- this had been going on for over an hour and a half.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She closed her book with a grumble and looked around the living room she sat in: the rows of books and movies on shelves were absent, save for a couple sitting by themselves next to the television; the paintings which once sat on the walls were removed and all sat in a stack on the side of the room with many towers of cardboard boxes accompanying them. Elster had finally managed to find a bigger apartment for the three while they still tried for more, and thanks to a little behind-the-scenes ‘encouragement’ from Falke, the apartment supervisor offered it to them at an extremely competitive rate. She knew Elster and Ariane tried to avoid altering their new reality as much as possible, to maintain a feeling of realness and not blind fantasy, but Falke was always willing to bend the rules a little just for them.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Because they deserved it.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;They would be moving at the end of the season, but until then, it was business as usual, and for Elster and Ariane, there was a lot of business to be had.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke felt another reverberation coming from the bedroom and tensed up just as the whisper reached her ears.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;A plentiful amount of business, indeed.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane joked to her while Elster was out of earshot that they wanted to ‘make the most of the mattress’ before they left for their new place, but so far it seemed as though they were just excited about moving to an apartment where they would have room for their eventual family, and that excitement led to other forms of excitement.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;And Falke was excited too, even as she tried to hide and bottle it.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster and Ariane had noticed. They had invited her to join them on more than one occasion, and she already regularly slept through the night with them both, but joining them in that way-&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She didn’t feel she was ready.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;But she wanted to be.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke closed her eyes and breathed deeply in and out. Replika were not programmed to feel these kinds of physical desires, let alone feelings like love and yearning, and she was woefully under-equipped to deal with them herself. But damn it if she didn’t try.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Her forehead crystals softly glowed as she constructed a space for her to feel the things she wanted so badly. A Gestalt body modeled after her biosynthetic one: commandingly tall, thin, lithe, limbs graceful as a dancer’s. She laid her simulacra atop a pillowy bed and tried to pleasure herself. She rubbed up and down every part of her that ached for touch, ran her fingers up and down a body that begged for intimacy, and even found herself with her hands clenched around her neck, fighting for control over a body that she created but was not hers.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;It wasn’t enough; all she could do was wish they were another’s hands.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Still, it was a good start, but as she tried to bring Elster and Ariane into her space to complete her desire she kept messing up details about them. Their faces were blank, hands too small or too large, and bodies sometimes twisted or deformed.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;They weren’t real like the women in the room just next to her, and no matter how hard she tried, her mind rejected her built fantasy.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke opened her eyes to the sound of a door opening, but only stared blankly at the now blank television across from her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“...Falke, are you alright?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster’s voice finally reached her and she blinked rapidly. “I am fine, yes, yes,” she said, having to turn her head in multiple directions before she found which angle Elster looked at her from. Her hair was very frazzled and messy, and her eyes a bit dulled from exhaustion, but what immediately jumped out the most to Falke was that she only wore a pair of loose pyjama bottoms. This left her completely topless, presenting a veritable cornucopia of a body that begged for her attention; she fought against the urge to not be seen staring at her well-defined rows of abdominal muscles glistening with a light sheen of sweat, her thick, corded arms as she stretched her equally fierce shoulders, or her round, full, endlessly squeezable breasts, adorned with her perky, firm nipples.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke was born with the essence of godhood instilled in her, an attitude that was only encouraged and enforced by the dozens of controllers and Protektors who served directly under her, but to Falke, the very fact that a perfectly chiselled being in both mind and body such as Elster before her wasn’t being actively worshipped felt profane to her, and she begged herself to be allowed to be the one to do so.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster scratched the back of her head and frowned as she fought back a yawn. “I had to call out to you three times before you answered. Are you sure you’re okay?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke quickly put a hand up to her lips as she feigned a light cough, but it still took her a while to answer Elster again, she was too preoccupied by new sounds coming from the bathroom next to the bedroom: a running faucet, and someone who could only be Ariane gargling water, followed by a heavy spit. She did this thrice before she finally exited the bathroom for the bedroom again, during which Falke took in a slow breath and exhaled quickly, trying to compartmentalize and push aside the mental image screaming into her head from the knowledge of what Ariane must have been doing in bed with Elster. However, as Ariane left the bathroom, she briefly saw Falke and Elster in the living room and silently waved at them, meaning Falke also saw her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane’s hair was also a mess, showing frazzles in every direction, but her eyes and smile carried an energy of yearning for more, made even more apparent when she blew Elster a playful kiss. But yet again, what caught Falke’s attention the most was what Ariane was wearing, or rather, what she wasn’t. She had on only her semi-transparent nightgown, which months ago would not have even batted an eye, but it was a small piece of lingerie meant for a small body, and wonderful, peaceful domesticity had certainly caught up to the snow-haired woman. It certainly helped that her new partner Falke was more than willing to cook for her and Elster any amount and frequency of gourmet meals she was born with the knowledge of.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke only saw Ariane for a couple of seconds before she dipped back into the bedroom, but that was enough to see that the hem of the nightgown which had once gone comfortably below her buttocks now sat almost right in the centre line of her hips, and there was more to discover as she turned to blow her kiss to Elster. Falke almost gasped as she saw Ariane’s nightgown now didn’t even fully cover her still visibly moist and bare folds, and the front of the garment, slick with sweat, stuck to her body in such a way that it didn’t not hide any of her newly developing luscious curves, including the small, but growing pouch of her tummy which all knew would only grow even more should their efforts in the bedroom succeed. She had seen it lightly spilled over the waistband of jeans and shorts before, but seeing the full picture alongside the visible outline of her also widening navel and the sheer radiance of Ariane’s being once again compelled Falke’s blasphemous urge to worship.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke struggled to not sigh. They were both perfect in every way. So much more perfect than her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She coughed again once Ariane had left and she had pulled her mind out of its spiral of desire and self-doubt. “It’s alright,” she assured Elster. “Just had my mind pre-occupied,” she half-lied.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster nodded and went to sit down on the spot next to her on the couch. Just her hip brushing up against hers sent lightning bolts through her body, but then Elster put her hand atop her knee, and she had to fight not to shudder greatly against this innocent contact.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster blinked strongly before she sighed, fidgeting her legs as she sat. “Well… well… um…” She paused to exhale slowly. “Are you ready for bed? Ari isn’t very tired, but I could probably…”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“You’re not finished?” Falke croaked.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster didn’t answer verbally, but bit her lip and slowly raised her hands and shoulders into a hesitant shrug.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke nodded. “Take your time,” she said.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster also nodded and slowly stood up, but soon after she started walking back to the bedroom she spun around and looked almost pleadingly at Falke.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Do you think-”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Thank you, but… not yet,” Falke finished for her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster sighed and gave her a thumbs-up before she rounded the corner. A moment later she heard the door click shut again, and she picked up her book.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She got the same amount of reading done through this session as well: a singular, rather short page.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane came out around twenty minutes later to find Falke staring at the blank television once again, only this time, she was alert enough to notice when she had entered the living room and turned and smiled at her once she came fully into view. Internally, Falke breathed a silent sigh of relief that Ariane had swapped her sweat-slicked nightgown for one of Elster’s larger t-shirts, the long, opaque garment thankfully reaching low enough to cover everything her increasingly too-small nightgown failed to.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“We’re uh, heading to bed now,” Ariane informed her, letting out a short yawn after she finished.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The question wasn’t asked, but statements like this one implied it: did Falke want to sleep with them tonight? She was comfortable enough to do so on occasion, usually taking up the outer side of any cuddle pile they organized and forming a basket with her long arms and legs to wrap around both Elster and Ariane.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke looked down for a moment. She wasn’t sure if being near the two wives would be such a good idea while she was still burdened by desire, but as she briefly glanced back up at Ariane’s eyes and saw the optimistic glow in her eyes, she felt like she had to say yes.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;So, she nodded and stood up, and Ariane gave a short hop of excitement before pressing her palms together; Falke almost felt her systems seize up for a brief moment as Ariane’s impromptu hop sparked a noticeable ripple up her thighs, tummy, and finally chest, still visible even through the loose shirt which mostly hung off her shoulders.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Falke, you coming?” Ariane asked, snapping her out of her uncontrollable thoughts.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She blinked and caught back up to Ariane, who smiled once they were side-by-side. Then, on pure instinct, Falke brought her arms up just as Ariane leaped into them, her reflexes knowing what she would do even before she did. Ariane nuzzled against Falke’s shoulder as she carried her into the bedroom, yawning once again as she carefully laid her down atop the mattress. On the far side was Elster, splayed out on her back fast asleep with the covers only partially across her legs; Falke tried not to stare at her exposed upper body and restart her spiraling, only watching Ariane as she carefully moved Elster’s arm to her side before she wiggled into place in the middle of the bed, leaving a space to her other side just for her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Once she was in, Ariane wasted no time in playing little spoon to Falke’s big spoon, and she sighed peacefully as she settled into place and Falke pulled the covers up the three with her bioresonance. As she wrapped her arms around Ariane, skipping Elster for now to avoid waking her up, Ariane brought her hand to her lips and kissed the backs of her fingers, sending a light shockwave of sensation up her arm and throughout her body with every touch.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Can you believe we have all of this?” Ariane whispered. “I still have trouble believing it from time to time.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke held Ariane a little more snugly. “Truthfully, I have a hard time remembering many details of my past life… it is as if I started here, with you both,” she whispered back.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane turned her head slightly to the side, managing to get a peek at Falke’s face from the corner of her eye. “Because of the whole issue of having our memories?” she asked.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“No, at least, not entirely,” Falke answered, pausing to kiss the top of Ariane’s head. “It is more… I was not an individual before this. I was… a symbol, a divine one, indeed, but still ultimately a symbol. I was given a role to play, and I played it… so many seasons of nothing but administrative monotony, never being allowed to form connections, to seek out life and change, or stray from my path in any way. I was a god, but I was just as confined and trapped as every other Replika and Gestalt at the facility… but now I am free. I am liberated to be whoever I want to be. It is the start of a life, or at the very least, a new one.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“But…” Ariane returned her head forward and sank back into Falke’s body. “Have you not just traded one aspect of desire for another? Our desires?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke found Ariane’s hand and held it firmly. “I chose to be here with you both, and you chose to have me as part of your lives. That is all that matters to me.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane took a short breath and exhaled softly. “Okay… thank you…”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Afterward, Elster snorted in her sleep, and her two partners realized jointly that it would be best to keep conversation to a minimum, lest they wake her up. Ariane brought Falke’s hand to her lips again and began to gently kiss each of the digits on her hand before moving to do the same to each of her knuckles.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I’m glad you chose to come here and be with us,” Ariane as quietly as possible whispered before she kissed the palm of Falke’s hand.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke smiled under Ariane’s kisses, but the longer she went on, the more curious her displays of affection grew. She started bringing her knuckles past her lips to suck on, followed by her finger tips. She reached for Falke’s thigh behind her and rubbed her hands up and down the smooth polyethylene shell, even giving her a light squeeze once. Then, she noticed Ariane start to wiggle her hips and legs together, sighing wistfully as she let go of her hand, and through it all, Falke felt more and more tense until she finally heard the telltale sounds of rhythmic, peaceful sleeping that signaled she was finally asleep.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke finally began to relax and nod off as well, shutting down her primary systems to enter sleep mode, but right in the middle of falling asleep she felt Ariane squirm ever so gently again and snapped back fully awake. She looked over Ariane’s cheek and saw she was still asleep, but also that she still continued to wiggle and pant.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Falke…” Ariane quietly muttered, moaning softly afterward. “Touch…” she added before sighing heavily and relaxing.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane quieted down and returned to sleep, but Falke only stared at the ceiling.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She didn’t get any more sleep that night.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;…..&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster was the first to wake up in the morning, though, with Falke never having truly fallen asleep, it might have been more accurate to say she was the second. She blinked her eyes open and almost immediately saw Falke to her left lying on her back, eyes open and unblinking toward the ceiling. She tried to lean forward but came to the realization that Ariane had shifted in her sleep, and had a significant portion of her body resting atop her, with her head planted almost face down into her chest.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Falke…?” she whispered. The Replika rolled over onto her shoulder and got a good view of the situation, smiling lightly at the picture of Ariane softly sleeping and snoring into Elster’s cleavage. “Mind giving me a hand?” Elster whispered, pointing at the sleeping beauty atop her. Falke nodded.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Her forehead crystals started to glow softly as she gently cupped the back of Ariane’s head with her hand and began to carefully roll Ariane onto her back using bioresonance.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Ellie… come back…” Ariane mumbled in her sleep as she came to a rest on her back, followed by more quiet, sleepy breathing. Elster cupped her mouth and tried not to giggle too loudly at her wife’s subconscious thoughts, but Falke bit her lip hard as she saw what Ariane was doing with her hand under the covers as she slept. She tugged the covers up past Ariane’s stomach to try and give her a modicum of privacy, but in doing so she only made Elster curious, and soon she leaned her head over to watch what her wife’s fidgeting arm was doing; she quickly snapped back and pressed her hand against her mouth.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Afterward a minute of quiet, awkward silence only punctuated by Ariane briefly snorting and groaning in her sleep, Falke deftly slipped out of bed and gave herself a light stretch; a mostly unnecessary thing to do for a Replika, but also a quirk of Gestalt neural imprinting that still felt right to do.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I will go prepare breakfast,” Falke quietly stated. Elster gave her a thumbs up.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I’ll stay here for… a bit… if that’s alright,” Elster answered, briefly looking down at the still-sleeping Ariane. Falke nodded and left the room, breathing a sigh of relief as the door clicked shut behind her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She briskly walked into the kitchen, hoping that absorbing herself in cooking would take her mind off things. Her bioresonance crystals shone brightly as she assembled her tools and ingredients: She grabbed a large metal bowl and whisk with her hands as the fridge opened and a carton of milk and a few eggs floated to her workstation, followed shortly after by tubs of sugar, flour, and salt, and finally a container of cooking oil. She carefully weighed all of her measurements on a kitchen scale before adding them one at a time to the bowl, finishing by tapping the eggs on the countertop and cracking them into the bowl. Falke wetted a cloth and wrung it out so it was just damp, wrapping it around the base of her metal bowl to keep it still as she furiously beat the mixture with a whisk.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She smiled; Ariane and Elster had an electric whisk she could have used, she had gotten it for