      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;A trans girl finds herself in a much less trans body, one that leaves her with little to no complaints... except the world she finds herself in sets her up in a very unaccommodating environment, where her great new life might find it's end rather quickly?!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;A story inspired by one specific artwork I came across. The protagonist is thrown into a cold-uncaring world, warmed only by a little star of hope. Please be aware of the tags if you want to avoid reading things you may be uncomfortable with.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1327453-otherworldly-thanksgiving-gone-wrong/chapter/1327463/"&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;Chapter 1&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;p lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us"&gt; &lt;div class="wi_authornotes"&gt; &lt;div&gt; &lt;div class="p-avatar-wrap"&gt;&lt;a class="avatar has-link" href="/profile/173089/lurker123/"&gt;&lt;img id="acc_ava_change profile" alt="" src="https://cdn.scribblehub.com/default/avatarnew.png"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="an_username"&gt;&lt;a href="/profile/173089/lurker123/"&gt;Lurker123&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div style="clear: both;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="wi_authornotes_body"&gt;  &lt;br /&gt;Hello dear reader!&lt;br /&gt;Welcome to the first story I've ever written down! And I'm putting it straight to the public, which may or may not turn out to be a bad idea.&lt;br /&gt;This is your last chance to turn away from what is probably the definition of underwhelming! Hopefully, me being an avid reader will do me &lt;em&gt;some &lt;/em&gt;good here.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us"&gt;For your information, text in &lt;em&gt;cursive&lt;/em&gt; is both for emphasis, as well as showing the literal inner thoughts of the MC as opposed to just descriptions of them. If it appears in spoken dialogue, it's only for emphasis. Is this good formatting? You tell me!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us"&gt;Last but not least, I won't put up specific trigger/content warnings for each chapter - the tags on the main page should clue you in on what's to come. Some may not get fulfilled until later, the tags just show what I know I'll be including.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us"&gt;Enjoy! (Or don't, I'll just go cry in a corner then...)&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
